&lt;p&gt;Band 7 – Sonographer – Diagnostic Imaging Department to support with Vascular Services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking to recruit enthusiastic, motivated, Band 7 sonographers to join our busy, friendly Ultrasound team at Kettering General Hospital NHS Foundation Trust. We provide a comprehensive (mainly non-obstetric) ultrasound service to a wide range of specialities and services in the hospital and for local GP’s.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Kettering General Hospital provides acute health care services to an ever growing population of around 280,000 in North Northamptonshire, South Leicestershire and Rutland. The majority of the services are delivered from our main site and satellite outpatient facilities at two neighbouring units.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As an employer of over 4000 staff, we are one of the biggest employers in Northamptonshire.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for suitable candidates to support with a range of vascular studies together with general abdominal, small parts, and musculoskeletal (preferred but not essential) services. You will be expected to work independently, however support from other sonographers is always available and encouraged.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You must be highly competent and keen to contribute towards efficient service delivery and excellent patient care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You must hold a UK recognised Pg. Diploma or Pg. Certificate in Medical Ultrasound and state registration with HCPC preferred but not essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Join us and you will be part of a community that recognises your contribution.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information please email Dr K Lakhani (PhD) Lead Sonographer on klakhani@nhs.net.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
